page.title: 12LANDSCAPE OF WARWICK BRIDGE
page.content: The area is mainly countryside. The river Eden winds its way through the fields, if you can afford it there is good salmon fishing. Round here the land is kept very well.You would find mixed woodland round here.In the villages you would find a few small shops. There is also a golf course. There is a main road. It is the A69.In some of the fields there is a plant called Oilseed rape which has a yellow flower.In other fields there is barley and turnips.The areas animals seem to be contented. You would find lots of little country lanes, old farmhouses, pasture fields, small estates of houses built in the last fifty years or so and peace and quiet....if you like that sort of thing.
